<subSubSection id="B161A82F928542907077BF83D95924F3" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" type="distribution and habitat">
<paragraph id="CE1992A3F32D53E06B5B62DC3831818E" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FB57DBED50C66E405BDD412763A96128" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">
<taxonomicName id="CC184A765E4A2842A075AA9E21389409" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Mecyclothorax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mecyclothorax interruptus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="interruptus">Mecyclothorax interruptus</taxonomicName>
is broadly distributed across the Waikamoi block of forest from 1170-1860 m elevation (Fig. 51). This species has been found by sifting 
<normalizedToken id="BF53AC1A4E15D266B9E5A6A9D07F748F" originalValue="‘ōhi‘a">'ōhi'a</normalizedToken>
leaf litter, searching under boards or logs on the ground, and by pyrethrin sampling moss-covered standing tree trunks and horizontal nurse logs.
</paragraph>
